description:
Test an arXiv identifier quant-ph/0001234 like this. An \([[n,k,d]]\) stabilizer code admitting a set of stabilizer generators that are either \(Z\)-type or \(X\)-type Pauli strings. The stabilizer generator matrix is of the form \begin{align}
H=\begin{pmatrix}0 & H_{Z}\\
H_{X} & 0
\end{pmatrix}
\label{eq:parity}
\tag*{(1)}\end{align} such that the rows of the two blocks must be orthogonal \begin{align}
H_X H_Z^T=0~.
\label{eq:comm}
\tag*{(2)}\end{align} The above condition guarantees that the \(X\)-stabilizer generators, defined in the symplectic representation as rows of \(H_X\), commute with the \(Z\)-stabilizer generators associated with \(H_Z\).

